---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import PostCard from '../components/PostCard.astro';
import TagFilter from '../components/TagFilter.astro';

type Frontmatter = {
  title: string;
  date: string;
  excerpt: string;
  tags: string[];
};

type PostModule = {
  frontmatter: Frontmatter;
  default: AstroComponentFactory; // Captures the rendered Markdown content
};

const allPostModules = import.meta.glob<PostModule>('../content/posts/*.md', { eager: true });

const posts = Object.entries(allPostModules)
  .map(([filePath, postModule]) => {
    const { frontmatter, default: Content } = postModule;
    const slug = filePath.split('/').pop()?.replace('.md', '') ?? '';
    return {
      slug,
      Content, // Pass the rendered content along with the frontmatter properties
      ...frontmatter
    };
  })
  .sort((a, b) => new Date(b.date).getTime() - new Date(a.date).getTime());

let allTagsSet = new Set<string>();
posts.forEach((post) => {
  if (Array.isArray(post.tags)) {
    post.tags.forEach((t) => allTagsSet.add(t));
  }
});
const allTags = [...allTagsSet];
---
<BaseLayout title="Home" description="Etcetera: Notes from the Middle of Thinking">
  <section style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    <p>Originally a space for open exploration and contemplation of unsolved problems in philosophy and science, Etcetera evolved into a space for mathematical growth. Mathematics, especially at the primary and secondary level, is often taught through rote memorization and drilling with an emphasis on speed. Read a question, recognize the keyword, execute an algorithm, repeat.</p>
    <p>However, mathematical research (my ultimate goal) requires a different toolkit: logical reasoning, lateral thinking, comfort with the uncomfortable, slow contemplation etc that this method doesn't train. In an effort to rectify this, I explore deliberately challenging mathematical problems – questions that require and consequently train those same skills research requires and share my entire process (including the dead-ends, failed approaches, insights etc) here. "Mathematics-ing-in-public" as I like to call it.</p>
    <p>Of course, feel free to join the journey: share your own approaches, show where you went wrong, tell what you learned, and even submit your own problems. Cheers!</p>
  </section>

  <TagFilter allTags={allTags} />

  {posts.length === 0 ? (
    <p>No posts found.</p>
  ) : (
    posts.map((post) => (
      <PostCard
        key={post.slug}
        title={post.title}
        date={post.date}
        slug={post.slug}
        tags={post.tags}
        content={post.Content} // 👈 Pass the layout component directly down to the card
      />
    ))
  )}
</BaseLayout>